<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-05-22T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-05-22T16:00:00-05:00" n="226" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d226">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/1427: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Representative of the President</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-05-22T16:00:00-05:00">May
                                        22, 1939—4 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 6:54 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>55. Reference Legation’s telegram No. 53. The President of the
                                Commission is in full agreement that Ocheltree visit Tegucigalpa at
                                this time to present to the Government of Honduras the geographic
                                data which he suggests be referred further to as “some points which
                                have been considered by the Commission.” Department’s approval of
                                Ocheltree’s travel requested.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Corrigan</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>